title: Bulldogs Blowout Dragons, Break .500
text:
Bulldogs Blowout Dragons, Break .500 
By Norman Seawright III Bulldogs Blowout Dragons, Break .500 October 3, 2015 Updated Oct 3, 2015 at 9:38 PM CDT 
Moorhead, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) football team handily defeated Minnesota State University-Moorhead, winning back-to-back for the first time this season. 
The Bulldogs picked up 555 yards of total offense, with quarterback Drew Bauer rushing for 177 of the team's 335 yards (his highest since the NCAA II playoff game against Emporia State in 2013), and Beau Bofferding scoring three of the team's touchdowns.
